{{Infobox organization |name = Federation of European Nutrition Societies (FENS) |image = Federation of European Nutrition Societies FENS Logo.png |image_border = |size = |alt = |caption = |map = |msize = |malt = |mcaption =
|abbreviation = FENS |motto = |formation = 1979 |extinction = |type = [[Non-governmental organization|NGO]] |status = |purpose = |headquarters = |location = Madrid, Spain |region_served = Europe |membership = |language = English |leader_title = President |leader_name = Heiner Boeing, Germany |main_organ = |parent_organization = [[International Union of Nutritional Sciences]] |affiliations = |num_staff = |num_volunteers = |budget = |website = [http://www.fensnutrition.eu/ FENS Official website] |remarks = }}
The '''Federation of European Nutrition Societies (FENS)''' is a [[Nonprofit organization|non-profit association]], established in 1979 <ref>{{cite web |url= http://journals.cambridge.org/download.php?file=%2FPNS%2FPNS37_02%2FS0029665178000208a.pdf&code=29e9ebe17b999810d298f403f4d38dc7 |title= The history of The Nutrition Society |author= Alice M. Coppi |date=1978 |page= 22}}</ref> as a roof organization for the national [[nutrition]] [[societies]] in Europe, with each country represented by its representative Nutrition Society or Association within FENS.
The aims of FENS are the combination of efforts for the development of research and education in [[Nutrition science|Nutrition Sciences]] and the promotion of the importance of Nutrition for [[public health]] in [[Europe]]. It seeks to do this by coordinating the European nutrition societies at a European level, promoting and disseminating [[research]] and knowledge on nutrition sciences and facilitating nutrition learning and training, as well as scientific exchange across Europe.
FENS conducts every 4 years its main event, the FENS European Nutrition Conference, which is organized by one of the FENS member societies, elected by the FENS General Assembly. All FENS Member [[Society|Societies]] and [[Professional association|Association]]s can take part in the [[bidding]] process for the organization of a FENS ENC.<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.fensnutrition.eu/index.php?p=inicio&sec=statutes |title= Statutes of the Federation of European Nutrition Societies, 3rd update|author= FENS General Assembly |date=2011 |page= 1 (E)}}</ref>
The Federation of European Nutrition Societies is a member of the [[International Union of Nutritional Sciences|International Union of Nutritional Sciences (IUNS)]] <ref>IUNS Adhering Bodies FENS: [http://www.iuns.org/affiliated_bodies/federation-of-european-nutrition-societies-fens IUNS Affiliated Bodies]</ref> and the official FENS Journal is the “Annals of Nutrition and Metabolism”<ref>Annals of Nutrition and Metabolism ([https://www.researchgate.net/journal/1421-9697_Annals_of_Nutrition_and_Metabolism Ann Nutr Metabol)]</ref> ([[Impact factor|IF]] 2014/2015: 2.618)
