Computerized '''pharmacy management systems''' put patient profiles, medication, inventory, pricing, and other essential information within easy access for pharmacists and [[pharmacy technician]]s. The programs automate elements such as label printing, inventory management, stock reordering and billing.<ref name=PharmacyTech>{{Cite book| url=https://books.google.com/?id=GSEjDQAAQBAJ&pg=PR10&dq=%22like+label+printing,+inventory+management,+stock+reordering%22#v=onepage&q=%22like%20label%20printing%2C%20inventory%20management%2C%20stock%20reordering%22&f=false | title=The Pharmacy Technician| isbn=9781617315572| publisher=Perspective Press| date=2016}}</ref> As a result, pharmacies are more time-efficient, and dispense more prescriptions and information while ensuring the safe and effective use of pharmaceutical drugs.<ref>http://www.academia.edu/download/33169467/PHARMACY_MANAGEMENT_PROJECT_Ahmad_Ibitoye.docx {{dead link|date=September 2018}}</ref> Pharmacy computer software is usually purchased ready made or provided by a drug wholesaler as part of their service. Various pharmacy software operating systems are used throughout the many practice settings of pharmacy across the world.<ref name=PharmacyTech/><ref name="Inc.2017">{{cite book|author=DAA Enterprises, Inc.|title=Pharmacy Management Software for Pharmacy Technicians: A Worktext - E-Book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=8bA1DwAAQBAJ|date=13 September 2017|publisher=Elsevier Health Sciences|isbn=978-0-323-48498-5}}</ref><ref>{{Cite book| url=https://books.google.com/?id=i0BuCgAAQBAJ&pg=PR11&dq=%22used+throughout+the+many+practice+settings+of+pharmacy%22#v=onepage&q=%22used%20throughout%20the%20many%20practice%20settings%20of%20pharmacy%22&f=false | title=Clerical and Data Management for the Pharmacy Technician| isbn=9781285225821| last1=Quiett| first1=Linda| date=2012}}</ref>

