{{Infobox lake | name = Yovkovtsi Reservoir | image = | caption = | image_bathymetry = | caption_bathymetry = | location = | coords = {{coord|42.931|25.797|type:waterbody|display=inline,title}} | lake_type = [[reservoir]] | inflow = [[Veselina River]] | outflow = [[Veselina River]] | catchment = | basin_countries = Bulgaria | length = {{convert|7.5|km|abbr=on}} (from map) | width = {{convert|850|m|abbr=on}} | area = {{convert|574|ha|abbr=on}} (taken from 57400dka?? in WikiMania) | depth = | max-depth = {{convert|60|m|abbr=on}} (from dam) | volume = {{convert|92.2|hm3|acre.ft|abbr=on}} | residence_time = | shore = | elevation = | islands = | cities = }} The '''Yovkovtsi Reservoir''' (язовир „Йовковци“) is situated in northeastern [[Bulgaria]], {{convert|5|km}} away of the town of [[Elena (town)|Elena]]. It was built 20 years ago on the [[Veselina River]]. The reservoir is located in the territory of Elena municipality, and supplies water to [[Veliko Tarnovo]], [[Gorna Oryahovitsa]], [[Lyaskovets]], [[Strazhitsa]], [[Zlataritsa]], [[Elena (town)|Elena]], [[Gabrovo]] and [[Dryanovo]]. {{convert|223|km²}} of the reservoir are hygienic protected zone. The dam is rich in [[carp]], [[pikeperch]] and many other kinds of fish.
It is named after the prominent writer [[Yordan Yovkov]].
